## Interpretation

The controlled offsets do not produce a useful readback comb. Fixed reconstructions either tie direct or worsen the clean substrate residual. The only consistent zero-target improvement comes from choosing the corrected sample closest to zero, which is a target-aware calibration-zero selector rather than independent information about the substrate residual.

This answers the offset question negatively for precision: offsets can decorate or clean zero residuals, but the tested comb does not recover a better underlying read than the direct path.

